<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910305-0026</DOCNO><DOCID>910305-0026.</DOCID><HL>   BSN Files for Offering   Of 71% Stake in a Unit</HL><DATE>03/05/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BSN</CO><IN>SPECIALTY APPAREL RETAILERS (SAP)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)STOCK AND BOND REGISTRATIONS, PRICINGS (REG)</IN><LP>   DALLAS -- BSN Corp. said it registered with the Securitiesand Exchange Commission to offer about three million shares,or about 71%, of its Sport Supply Group unit.   BSN, a sporting goods concern, said it will use proceedsto pay back a $27.5 million loan from Citibank, eliminatingits bank debt.</LP><TEXT>   Sport Supply Group, a sports-equipment catalog company,had about $44 million in revenue last year, or almost half ofBSN's $90 million in revenue. In addition to Sport Supply,BSN owns a trophy business and a football equipment company.   BSN said it may consider paying a special dividend to itsholders or buying a &quot;significant quantity&quot; of its shares ordebt outstanding, depending on the size of the offering andits ability to find a new bank lender. BSN also said itexpects to report a pretax gain of $8 million from thetransaction. PaineWebber Inc. is managing the underwriting.</TEXT></DOC>